              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Recurring events like annual award seasons, sporting seasons, and tax deadlines are predictable. Use Google Trends to identify rising topics. Breaking news is unpredictable — responding to it fast requires a pre-built publishing workflow rather than ad hoc responses.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What types of content benefit most from QDF?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Breaking news, product launch coverage, event results, regulatory changes, and annual comparison guides ("best X in 2026") benefit most. Evergreen how-to content is almost never QDF-sensitive.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is QDF still active in 2026?</span>
